Rule: Education Level: Individuals with a Doctorate degree are more likely to earn more than $50,000 a year.
Occupation: Occupations in the 'Professional' category are associated with higher income predictions.
Work Hours (Self-Employed): Self-employed individuals working significantly more hours per week (e.g., 94 hours) are more likely to earn more than $50,000 a year.
Gender: Gender may influence income prediction outcomes, with males potentially being more likely to earn more than $50,000 a year in certain occupations.
Type of Employment: Being employed by the government or being self-employed can positively impact income prediction.
